<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q8_v13" title="Q8_v13" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>Registro del caso:</p><p>En un desayuno se prepararán varios vasos de un jugo mixto, utilizando jugo de piña y agua. La cantidad de cada ingrediente por vaso se indica en la siguiente lista:</p>
    <p>
      • Jugo de piña: 
      <m:math>
        <m:mfrac>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn>
          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
        </m:mfrac>
      </m:math>
      onzas por vaso<br />
      • Agua: 
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
      </m:math>
      onzas por vaso<br />
      • Se prepararán 
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>180</m:mn>
      </m:math>
      vasos en total<br />
      • Se considera que 
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
        <m:mtext> onza</m:mtext>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:mn>30</m:mn>
        <m:mtext> mL</m:mtext>
      </m:math>
    </p>
    <p>¿Cuál de las siguientes cantidades totales de jugo de piña, en mL, es compatible con los datos anteriores?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">3600 mL<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El jugo de piña total es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mtext> onzas por vaso</m:mtext><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>180</m:mn><m:mtext> vasos</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>270</m:mn><m:mtext> onzas</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>. Luego, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>270</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8100</m:mn><m:mtext> mL</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>. Por lo tanto, 3 600 mL no es compatible con los datos.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">8100 mL<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La cantidad total de jugo de piña es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mtext> onzas por vaso</m:mtext><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>180</m:mn><m:mtext> vasos</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>270</m:mn><m:mtext> onzas</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>. Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> onza</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mtext> mL</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>, se obtiene <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>270</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8100</m:mn><m:mtext> mL</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>, que coincide con esta opción.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">10800 mL<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El jugo de piña total es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mtext> onzas por vaso</m:mtext><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>180</m:mn><m:mtext> vasos</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>270</m:mn><m:mtext> onzas</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>, y <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>270</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8100</m:mn><m:mtext> mL</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>. En cambio, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>10&#160;800</m:mn><m:mtext> mL</m:mtext><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>360</m:mn><m:mtext> onzas</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>, que no coincide con las 270 onzas de jugo de piña.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">18900 mL<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El jugo de piña total debe ser <m:math><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mtext> onzas por vaso</m:mtext><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>180</m:mn><m:mtext> vasos</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>270</m:mn><m:mtext> onzas</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>. Al convertir, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>270</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>8100</m:mn><m:mtext> mL</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>. Además, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>18&#160;900</m:mn><m:mtext> mL</m:mtext><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>630</m:mn><m:mtext> onzas</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>, valor que no es compatible con los datos.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar la cantidad de jugo de piña por vaso</strong></p>
            <p>Cada vaso contiene:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:mfrac>
                <m:mtext> onzas de jugo de piña</m:mtext>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular la cantidad total de jugo de piña en onzas</strong></p>
            <p>Como se preparan 180 vasos, multiplicamos:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  </m:mfrac>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>180</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mn>540</m:mn>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  </m:mfrac>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>270</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces, en total se necesitan 270 onzas de jugo de piña.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Convertir de onzas a mL</strong></p>
            <p>El enunciado indica que:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> onza</m:mtext>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>30</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> mL</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>270</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> onzas</m:mtext>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>30</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> mL</m:mtext>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>8&#160;100</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> mL</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La cantidad total de jugo de piña compatible con los datos es <strong>8 100 mL</strong>.</p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>ChoiceB</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>